articles.summary:
Wirestock/iStock Editorial via Getty Images

Panasonic Holdings (
OTCPK:PCRFY
) has accelerated plans to expand production of electric vehicle batteries at a factory in Nevada jointly operated with Tesla (
NASDAQ:
TSLA
), according to Nikkei Asian Review.

The Japanese electronics, reportedly responding to 
pressure
 from Tesla (
TSLA
) for more battery production, will install a 15th production line at the Gigafactory in Nevada. The new line is scheduled to begin operation in one to two years.
